Q.1 Describe the Case study on cyber security risk management .Explain the control architecture and supporting processes" [15M]
Case Study Overview:
•	Scenario: A fintech bank wants to secure its digital banking platform against cyber threats, including data breaches, malware, phishing, and unauthorized access.
•	Goal: Protect customer financial data, ensure regulatory compliance, and maintain service availability.
Control Architecture:
1.	Preventive Controls:
•	Firewalls: Filter network traffic to block unauthorized access.
•	Encryption: Secure sensitive data in transit and at rest.
•	Access Control: Role-based access to limit system privileges.
•	Security Awareness Training: Educate employees on phishing and social engineering attacks.
2.	Detective Controls:
•	Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS): Monitor networks for suspicious activity.
•	Security Information and Event Management (SIEM): Centralized log monitoring for anomaly detection.
•	Vulnerability Scanning: Regular scanning of systems and applications to detect weaknesses.
3.	Corrective Controls:
•	Patch Management: Regularly update software to fix known vulnerabilities.
•	Incident Response Plan: Procedures for mitigating and recovering from security incidents.
Supporting Processes:
•	Risk Assessment: Identify, quantify, and prioritize cybersecurity risks.
•	Policy Management: Define security policies and ensure adherence.
•	Continuous Monitoring: Track security events in real-time for early detection.
•	Compliance Audits: Ensure adherence to PCI DSS, RBI PSS, and PSD2 standards.
Outcome:
•	Reduced risk of data breaches.
•	Compliance with regulatory standards.
•	Improved trust and confidence among customers.
Conclusion:
•	A structured cybersecurity control architecture combined with supporting processes ensures risk management, regulatory compliance, and secure fintech operations.
