Q.2 Mobile Banking vs Internet Banking and UPI [15M]
(a) Which is More Secure: Mobile Banking or Internet Banking? [5M]
•	Mobile Banking Security:
•	Typically more secure because it uses app-based authentication, biometric login (fingerprint, face recognition), and device binding.
•	Transactions are usually encrypted end-to-end.
•	Internet Banking Security:
•	Accessible via browsers; vulnerable to phishing attacks, malware, and keyloggers.
•	Conclusion: Mobile banking is generally considered more secure than internet banking.
________________________________________
(b) How Mobile Banking Works Without Internet [5M]
•	USSD (Unstructured Supplementary Service Data):
•	Mobile banking can work without internet using USSD codes (*99# in India for UPI).
•	Works on basic phones through secure session over GSM network.
•	SMS-based Transactions:
•	Certain banks allow balance inquiry, mini statements, and fund transfers using encrypted SMS commands.
•	Advantages: Accessible to users without smartphones or mobile data.
________________________________________
(c) Which Technology is Used in UPI? [5M]
•	UPI (Unified Payments Interface) Technology:
1.	API-based Architecture: Connects banks, fintech apps, and third-party providers.
2.	IMPS (Immediate Payment Service): Enables real-time fund transfers.
3.	Encryption: End-to-end encryption for transaction security.
4.	Two-Factor Authentication: Mobile number + MPIN for secure authorization.
•	Outcome: Fast, secure, and interoperable digital payments.





