Q.2 Introduction to Compliance within Fintech [15M]
(a) Describe Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (PCI DSS) [7–8M]
•	Definition: Global security standard designed to protect cardholder data during payment transactions.
•	Key Requirements:
1.	Build and maintain a secure network (firewalls, network segmentation).
2.	Protect cardholder data through encryption and secure storage.
3.	Implement strong access control measures (role-based access).
4.	Regularly monitor and test networks for vulnerabilities.
5.	Maintain an information security policy for employees.
•	Importance in Fintech: Prevents data breaches, ensures secure card transactions, and maintains customer trust.
________________________________________
(b) Describe RBI PSS (Reserve Bank of India - Payment and Settlement Systems) [7–8M]
•	Definition: Framework by the Reserve Bank of India to regulate all payment and settlement systems in India.
•	Key Components:
1.	RTGS (Real-Time Gross Settlement): Instant settlement of high-value interbank transactions.
2.	NEFT (National Electronic Funds Transfer): Batch-based electronic retail payments.
3.	UPI (Unified Payments Interface): Instant mobile payments system.
4.	Clearing Systems: Netting and reconciliation between banks.
•	Compliance Guidelines:
•	Banks must follow RBI operational standards, maintain security, audit logs, and monitor fraud.
•	Importance in Fintech: Ensures secure, efficient, and regulated payment services in India.













